                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13267459" author="dagw" created="Thu, 3 May 2012 15:25:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Both XCY05.S.1 and XCY05.S.3 need adjustment. Perhaps also XCY05.S.2: &quot;has already been set&quot; should perhaps be &quot;has already been implicitly/automatically set&quot; ..?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13267644" author="rhillegas" created="Thu, 3 May 2012 19:15:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching derby-5742-01-aa-rewordMessage.diff. This changes the wording for the error condition. Here is the new wording:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Invalid setting of the derby.authentication.provider property. To enable NATIVE authentication, please use the SYSCS_UTIL.SYSCS_CREATE_USER procedure to store credentials for the database owner.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13267659" author="rhillegas" created="Thu, 3 May 2012 19:23:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The other two error messages look ok to me. XCY05.S.1 would be thrown if you tried to set derby.authentication.provider=NATIVE::GLOBAL. XCY05.S.2 would be thrown if you tried to set derby.authentication.provider=LDAP after NATIVE authentication had been enabled. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13267717" author="chaase3" created="Thu, 3 May 2012 20:21:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;You could drop &quot;please&quot; &amp;#8211; we avoid it in documentation. We&apos;re polite enough. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13268302" author="rhillegas" created="Fri, 4 May 2012 13:43:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Kim. Attaching derby-5742-01-ab-rewordMessage.diff, which removes the extra courtesy. Committed at subversion revision 1333915.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13268338" author="dagw" created="Fri, 4 May 2012 14:09:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Rick! The change looks for good for XXCY05.S.3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; XCY05.S.1: &quot;Invalid setting of the derby.authentication.provider property. NATIVE::LOCAL is the only NATIVE value accepted by derby.authentication.provider.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well, we never do accept &quot;NATIVE::LOCAL&quot; as an explicitly set value anymore, do we? Quoting from the spec 7.0:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;NATIVE::LOCAL - This value is never explicitly set by an application. It is ignored if it is set via JVM properties or via derby.properties.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, I still think the wording is misleading.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13268366" author="rhillegas" created="Fri, 4 May 2012 14:52:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Dag,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How about this text for XCY05.S.1: &quot;Invalid setting of the derby.authentication.provider property.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13273660" author="dagw" created="Fri, 11 May 2012 23:09:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Rick! That&apos;s fine, I think. +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
